{"lemma":"ضَلالٌ","slug":"ضَلالٌ","root":"ض.ل.ل","root_slug":"ض-ل-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ض-ل-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ضَلال","root":"ضلل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":38},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n25935"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B6%D9%8E%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ضَلَّ (ḍalla) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n25935","headword_ar":"ضَلَالٌ","root":"Dl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[an inf. n. of 1: used as a simple subst.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Error; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ra$aAdN","text_ar":"رَشَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hudFY","text_ar":"هُدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DalaAlapN","text_ar":"ضَلَالَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dal~N","text_ar":"ضَلٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dul~N","text_ar":"ضُلٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dil~apN","text_ar":"ضِلَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DalalN","text_ar":"ضَلَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaloDalapN","text_ar":"ضَلْضَلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DulaDilapN","text_ar":"ضُلَضِلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uDoluwlapN","text_ar":"اُضْلُولَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) of which last the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDaAliylu","text_ar":"اَضَالِيلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, O, TA,) as in the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamaAdaY fiY A^aDaAliyli AlhawaY","text_ar":"تَمَادَى فِى اَضَالِيلِ الهَوَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He persevered in the errors of love"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDaAliylu","text_ar":"اَضَالِيلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as some say, has no sing., or its sing. is supposed, or has been heard, and is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uDoluwlapN","text_ar":"اُضْلُولَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uDoluwlN","text_ar":"اُضْلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iDoliylN","text_ar":"اـِضْلِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or some other form: (MF, TA:) the primary signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~alaAlu","text_ar":"الضَّلَالُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the going away from the right course,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"direction:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 357:) or it signifies, accord. to Ibn-El-Kemál,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the loss,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"missing, of that which brings,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conducts, to the object sought:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the pursuing a way that will not bring,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conduct, to that object:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to Er-Rághib,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the deviating from the right way:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and it is said to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any deviation from that which is right, intentional"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unintentional, little"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the right and approved way is very difficult; wherefore it may be used of him who commits any mistake whatever, and is imputed to prophets and to unbelievers, though between the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DlAl","text_ar":"ضلال"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the former and that of the latter is a wide difference: and in another point of view, it is of two sorts; one is in the speculative departments of knowledge, as in acquaintance with the unity of God, and with the prophetic function or office, and the like, indicated in the Kur iv. 135; or it is in the practical departments of knowledge, as in acquaintance with the ordinances of the law, that is, religious services. (TA.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A state of perdition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the Kur liv. 24: (S, O:) [and in like manner ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DalaAlapN","text_ar":"ضَلَالَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DalaAlapu AlEamali","text_ar":"ضَلَالَةُ العَمَلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The annulled and lost state of work."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Absence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a state of concealment."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb. [This is there said to be the primary signification.]) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa AlD~alaAlu bonu Alt~alaAli","text_ar":"هُوَ الضَّلَالُ بْنُ التَّلَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"see expl. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dul~N","text_ar":"ضُلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","O","TA","K","Lth","MF"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}